    <stitle>SUSPENSION ALIGNMENT - REAR AXLE ADJUSTMENT - HENDRICKSON (WITHOUT BAR PIN DESIGN)</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="adjust" graphiccount="0">
        <title>HENDRICKSON (WITHOUT BAR PIN DESIGN)</title>
        <para>This design of Hendrickson suspensions does not provide for axle adjustment for alignment purposes. If the
            axles are measured to be significantly out of alignment, the following areas should be investigated as the
            possible cause and corrected as necessary.
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Severely worn walking beam center or end bushings.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Worn spring pins.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Improper location of frame brackets on frame.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Any other worn or damaged parts.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
